  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nPublic chats are missing messages, that are not recovered even after multiple history requests.\r\n\r\nI suspect that the problem is in the way we query history from mail servers. As I understood from the discussion in Status.im we do it in a following way: If at first I query envelopes from 13:10:11 till 13:15:17 and query was successful, next time i will start my query from 13:15:17 till some timestamp. The problem is that mail server can receive a message with timestamp lower than 13:15:17 after we sent back a history for 1st query.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nMail server uses (Expiry timestamp - TTL) as a timestamp for the message. Additionally there is small time window that is tolerated by any whisper node, afair it is 10s. I would suggest to adjust query with a common TTL and mentioned whisper window. \r\n\r\nIt will increase rate of duplicates, but we will stop missing messages from mail server.\r\n\r\n# Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nMessages that are received by mail server after history was queried should be sent to the user on a subsequent queries.\r\n\r\nlink: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/6757\r\n",
